OL,3,CChief of Police perjury claims to be
OL,4,Cinvestigated by UK force
OL,6,FHe explains: "That associated
OL,7,Fcomplaint was concluded on the basis
OL,8,Fthat it appeared 'frivolous, vexatious
OL,9,For otherwise an abuse of process'.
OL,11,F"It is important not to predetermine
OL,12,Fthe outcome of this new complaint
OL,13,Fprior to investigation on its own
OL,14,Fmerits.
OL,16,F"However, we wanted to raise this to
OL,17,Freassure the public that a complaint
OL,18,Fbeing investigated by an external
OL,19,Fpolice force does not suggest that the
OL,20,FChief Officer has committed any
OL,21,Fdisciplinary or criminal offence."
